hate cats who here hates cats and why by the way to the th answerer i do have a cat and it insists upon being near me even though i don't like it it's really my husband's i feed it and water it when he's not around but he does the rest my dog does not drool but i know what you mean about the bigger dogs that do it's gross this cat does nothing but hiss sit on the window sill scratch the furniture smell up the place with its litter box and leaves hair all over the place my dog doesn't shed when it scratches my daughter it does it on purpose whereas my dog does it by accident and would never intend to hurt her i do agree hate's a strong word i'd never hurt the cat but i don't like their slinkiness and attitude at all i will be picking my fave answer shortly it's a tough choice ps number that thumbs down did not come from me you got a thumbs up so did all but two others no thumbs down from me for answering ever i don't hate cats but i do dislike them dogs are just so much friendlier i'm not saying you won't find a friendly cat out there but affectionate cats are rare sure they'll purr when you pet them but dogs will come running for a cuddle the second they hear you come home i think the key difference between the two is loyalty dogs are faithful they'll come when called protect you when you're in danger or when they think you're in danger my dog once tried to defend me from a table i was carrying and find their way home when they're lost cats just walk around the house doing their own thing they don't give you that warm and fuzzy feeling of being adored like dogs do Cat Dog Treecat Characters of Lost Hamster Maison Ikkoku The Death Gate Cycle Fruits Basket Garfield Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) RuneScape quests Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Ranma __ characters Get Fuzzy Shaggy dog story Domestic rabbit Team Rocket Guinea pig Catscratch Poker jargon Kodocha Phoebe Buffay's songs English grammar Dilbert Ren and Stimpy The Cat in the Hat Trailer Park Boys The Amber Spyglas